      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Friday ¶ Letter dated to 28 September, the Friday beforeThursday4 October when M was planning to leave for WA(see M to G. Berry, 26 September 1877). ¶  ¶ For the sake of my health, dear Mr Shillinglaw...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.09.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Shillinglaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Box 244/3, Shillinglaw papers, La Trobe Australian manuscripts collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Friday</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Letter dated to 28 September, the Friday before<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Thursday<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>4 October when M was planning to leave for WA<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see M to G. Berry, 26 September 1877).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For the sake of my health, dear Mr Shillinglaw, I intend to do a few weeks field-work and shall be away at the middle of next week. Could I revise before any notes biographically concerning me?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Shillinglaw was preparing biographical notes for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the forthcoming work,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Men of the time</seg>; see M to J. Shillinglaw, September 1877<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 77-09-00a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I read with great interest in the "Sydney mail" your notes on the disinterment of the long buried documents emanating from Mr Grimes's discoveries.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.3541in; text-indent: -0.3541in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">m</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">ail</seg>, 22 September 1877, p. 376, carried a report of Shillinglaw's discovery in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the colonial archives in Sydney of Charles Grimes's journal and chart of his exploration of Port Phillip Bay and the lower reaches of the Yarra River in 1803.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>journal is included in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Shillinglaw (1879), pp.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>15-30.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
